<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title><%= title %></title>
  <script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/2.1.3/jquery.min.js"></script>
  <script src="/javascripts/index.js"></script>
  <link rel='stylesheet' href='/stylesheets/style.css' />
</head>
<body>

<h1><%= title %></h1>
  <div class="container">
    <p>
      Welcome. This whiteboard is real-time. I used Node.js as the server, Socket.io for real-time collaboration, Express as the web framework and HTML5 Canvas. It's so cool!
      I'm also trying to learn how to stream video across sockets, for not it's in the works but will crash my server if I let it run too long.
    </p>
    <div class="username-container">
      <form class="username">
        <p>Enter a username!</p>
        <label for="name">Name:</label>
        <input id="name" type="text"/>
        <input id="submit-name" type="submit"/>
      </form>
    </div>
    <% include partials/canvas %>
    <% include partials/chat %>
    <% include partials/video %>
  </div>
  <h6>Daniela</h6>
  <script src="https://cdn.socket.io/socket.io-1.3.5.js"></script>
  <script src="/javascripts/socket.io-stream.js"></script>
</body>
</html>









